---
description: Inserts a retrieval-grounded context block. The application substitutes <<RETRIEVED_CHUNKS>> with real chunks at runtime.
vars:
  - name: index_name
    type: string
    description: Name of the retrieval index to query. Lowercase, dashes only.
    pattern: "^[a-z0-9-]+$"
  - name: top_k
    type: int
    description: Number of chunks to retrieve from the index.
    min: 1
    max: 50
    default: 5
    required: false
  - name: chunk_separator
    type: string
    description: Separator placed between retrieved chunks in the rendered prompt.
    default: "\n---\n"
    required: false
---
## Retrieved context

The following passages were retrieved from the `{{ index_name }}` index
(top_k = {{ top_k }}). Use them to ground your answer; if the answer is not
supported by these passages, say so explicitly.

<<RETRIEVED_CHUNKS index={{ index_name }} k={{ top_k }} separator={{ chunk_separator | tojson }}>>
